data.name: TextBox3.Text
data.value:
Xenon the cloud locker helps you encrypt your files locally and store them on the cloud.
The Upload tab helps you to upload files to the cloud. To upload a file click on Browse and select the required file. Click on Upload to encrypt and upload your file to the cloud.
The Management tab deals with various management tweaks.
On the left list box you can view the files stored on the cloud. Similarly on the right list box you can view the downloaded files.
To download a file select a file from the left list box and click on the download button after the download is complete you will be prompted to decrypt the file. The decrypted files are stored in the Downloads folder of the current working directory.
To delete a file from the cloud select a file from the left list box and click on the delete button.
To refresh both lists click on the Refresh Lists button.
